<div class="main-content">
    <h1>Turkey's Most Beautiful Destinations</h1>
    <p>Discover Historical and Natural Beauties</p>

    <section>
        <h2>Istanbul</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/ayasofya.jpeg" alt="Hagia Sophia">
            <img src="~/images/sultanahmet-camii.jpg" alt="Blue Mosque">
            <img src="~/images/bogaz-koprusu.jpg" alt="Bosphorus Bridge">
        </div>
        <p>Istanbul is Turkey's largest and most populous city, spanning both Asia and Europe. The historical peninsula, with landmarks like Hagia Sophia, Blue Mosque, and Topkapi Palace, captivates visitors.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Cappadocia</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/Peri-Bacalari.jpg" alt="Fairy Chimneys">
            <img src="~/images/ozel-balon-turu.jpg" alt="Hot Air Balloon Tours">
            <img src="~/images/goreme-acik-hava-muzesi.jpeg" alt="Goreme Open Air Museum">
        </div>
        <p>Cappadocia is famous for its fairy chimneys and underground cities. You can enjoy unforgettable moments with breathtaking views on hot air balloon tours.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Antalya</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/konyaalti-plaji.jfif" alt="Konyaalti Beach">
            <img src="~/images/kaleici.jpg" alt="Kaleiçi">
            <img src="~/images/duden-selalesi.jpg" alt="Duden Waterfalls">
        </div>
        <p>Known as Turkey's tourism capital, Antalya is renowned for its stunning beaches, historical ruins, and luxury resorts.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Pamukkale</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/traverten-teraslari.jpg" alt="Travertine Terraces">
            <img src="~/images/hierapolis-antik-kenti.jfif" alt="Hierapolis Ancient City">
        </div>
        <p>Pamukkale is famous for its white travertine terraces and the ancient city of Hierapolis. Its natural beauty and historical structures attract many visitors.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Ephesus</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/Celsus-kutuphanesi.jpg" alt="Library of Celsus">
            <img src="~/images/ephesus_theatre.jpg" alt="Great Theatre">
            <img src="~/images/artemis-tapinagi.jpg" alt="Temple of Artemis">
        </div>
        <p>Ephesus is renowned for its ruins from the Roman period. The Temple of Artemis, one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World, is located here.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Bodrum</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/bodrum-kalesi.jpg" alt="Bodrum Castle">
            <img src="~/images/yatLimani-bodrum1.jpg" alt="Marina">
            <img src="~/images/bodrum-antiktiyatro.jpg" alt="Ancient Theatre">
        </div>
        <p>Bodrum is famous for its vibrant nightlife, luxurious marina, and historical ruins. Bodrum Castle and the Ancient Theatre are must-see attractions.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Fethiye</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/oludeniz.jpg" alt="Oludeniz">
            <img src="~/images/kelebekler_vadisi.JPG" alt="Butterfly Valley">
            <img src="~/images/likya-yolu-yuruyus.jpg" alt="Lycian Way">
        </div>
        <p>Fethiye is known for its stunning beaches and natural wonders. Places like Oludeniz Beach and Butterfly Valley enchant visitors.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Cesme</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/cesme-kalesi-1.jpg" alt="Cesme Castle">
            <img src="~/images/Cesme-Ilica-Plaji.jpeg" alt="Ilica Beach">
            <img src="~/images/alacati.jpg" alt="Alacati">
        </div>
        <p>Cesme is one of the popular holiday resorts of the Aegean Region. It is known for its clean beaches, historical castles, and luxury hotels.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Trabzon</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/uzungol-gezi-rehberi-600x450.jpg" alt="Uzungol">
            <img src="~/images/sumele-manastiri.jpg" alt="Sumela Monastery">
            <img src="~/images/trabzon-ayasofya-muzesi.jpg" alt="Hagia Sophia Museum (Trabzon)">
        </div>
        <p>Trabzon is known as the pearl of the Black Sea Region. It is famous for its natural and historical beauties such as Uzungol and Sumela Monastery.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Izmir</h2>
        <div class="destination">
            <img src="~/images/kordonboyu-izmir.jpg" alt="Kordonboyu">
            <img src="~/images/izmirin-tarihi-saat-kulesi.jpg" alt="Izmir Clock Tower">
            <img src="~/images/sirince-koyu-izmir-kapak.jpg" alt="Sirince">
        </div>
        <p>Izmir is Turkey's third-largest city. It stands out with its coastline, historical and cultural richness. Ephesus and Sirince Village are popular spots for visitors.</p>
    </section>
</div>

